sentences: Feeney was also a producer on albums by other Canadian country singers including Family Brown, and worked as a session musician before releasing his debut album Joel Feeney and the Western Front in 1991.
Feeney's second album Life Is but a Dream was released in 1993 and was produced by Chris Farren.
His most successful hit came in 1995 with "What Kind of Man", which topped the Canadian RPM country singles charts.
He is also notable for co-writing LeAnn Rimes' 2005 hit "Nothin' 'Bout Love Makes Sense".
This album was released by CBC audio in 2001
